saraba siberia tetsudo (Farewell, Siberian Railroad)
Hiromi Ohta

What lies on the far side of sadness? 
A white frozen plain where even tears freeze solid 
They say everyone hides winter 
Deep inside their hearts 
But no one is colder than you

I finished reading your letter and looked at the stamp
Small letters in Russian marked the postmark 
Searching for words to blame you 
For deciding on this breakup all alone 
I suddenly find myself chasing the northern sky

Please tell them for me, 
O traveler of December 
That I will wait... 
I will wait for them forever

What lies beyond these railroad tracks? 
The sorrowful eyes of a reindeer lost in the snow 
Growing weary of being led along 
By someone who offers no answers 
I jumped onto a tomorrow with no destination at all

I was too shy to say the word "love" 
And you, nearsighted, couldn't read the look in my eyes 
If people must learn to doubt 
Just to keep on living 
Then suddenly, they come to know the meaning of love

Please tell them for me, 
O traveler of December 
That I will wait... 
I will wait for them forever
